    "description": "Terra Drone Corporation, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the provision of industrial drone solutions. It operates through two segments, Aircraft Solutions and Aircraft Management. The company is involved in the development of unmanned aircraft system traffic management systems for enhancing the safety of drone and urban air mobility flights. The company also provides aerial solutions for spraying pesticides, fertilizers, and pest control products for agricultural plantations, as well as land survey and plant monitoring, mapping and analysis of soil conditions, and monitoring weather conditions and rainfall. In addition, it offers Terra UT drones and Terra 3D Inspect, a cloud-based platform for inspection of tanks, boilers, and various infrastructure facilities in the petrochemical and electric power industries. Further, the company provides Terra Lidar drones for construction and engineering, mining exploration, and GIS solutions. It serves land surveying, forest survey, mine surveying, infrastructure inspection, and oil and gas inspection sectors. The company has a strategic alliance with Quest UAV Ltd. Terra Drone Corporation was incorporated in 2016 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan."
